## Context
Two related issues found by distributed systems + DevOps reviews:

1. validate_tickets uses load_tickets(tickets/) which is non-recursive.
   After archival, a live ticket with Blocked-by: cm (where cm is in
   tickets/archive/) passes validation — the reference vanishes from
   all_ids silently.

2. archive DAG protection only scans tickets/ for references. If
   ticket A (archived) references ticket B (closed, old) via
   X-Discovered-from, B is unprotected in subsequent archive passes.

## Actions
1. In validate_all: also load tickets/archive/*.ticket into all_ids
   (but don't validate them — just use them as a reference set)
2. In find_archivable: also scan tickets/archive/*.ticket when
   building referenced_ids
3. Add tests for both scenarios

## Exit criteria
- Blocked-by referencing an archived ticket ID passes validation
- Archive DAG protection sees references from archived tickets
